    <Entry>
      <ID>7</ID>
      <DefaultText>Fatebinder Rhogalus,

How does one depict the death throes of a nation? In the [url=glossary:edict]Edict[/url] of Stone, [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url] consigned [url=glossary:cairn]Cairn[/url] to his doom, but in their ritual, the Earthshakers spread that execution across the entire region. The life drained from the soil even as it faded from [url=glossary:cairn]Cairn[/url]'s eyes.

One could verily feel the stone trying to leach my own life from me, as if I'd eaten stale bread when I already thirsted for a flagon. 

We marked this place, and it may never recover.

-Fatebinder [Player Name]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>8</ID>
      <DefaultText>Fatebinder Rhogalus,

The Archon [url=glossary:cairn]Cairn[/url] died with the [url=glossary:edict]Edict[/url] of Stone; the Earthshakers merely reclaimed their patron's power. As we carefully aligned crystalline shafts to channel incandescent energies, roiling auroras of magic twisted overhead. The air reverberated with chanting as the soil drank the blood of the [url=glossary:scarlet chorus]Scarlet Chorus[/url] who threw themselves ineffectually against our barricades.

No longer will the Earthshakers dally in the [url=glossary:stone sea]Stone Sea[/url], picking at the corpse of a rogue Archon. Now they bend their arcane might to the unification of the Tiers under a single banner.

In his final shuddering demise, [url=glossary:cairn]Cairn[/url] set the keystone for a new order.

- Fatebinder [Player Name]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>9</ID>
      <DefaultText>Fatebinder Rhogalus,

Whatever the Earthshakers hoped to accomplish with the remains of their errant Archon, I put an end to it. Robed magicians and ironclad warriors alike fell before the onslaught, their rituals cut off mid-chant. The power they drew forth from [url=glossary:cairn]Cairn[/url] roiled overhead, shuddering through the land as they collected it. The assault proved enough to disrupt the fragile spellwork, however, making of it a gaping wound. The magic flowed from the Archon of Stone as readily as the blood fled his acolytes, fulfilling the purpose of the Overlord's [url=glossary:edict]Edict[/url]. 

[url=glossary:cairn]Cairn[/url]'s execution was both savage and beautiful. I shall never forget it.

- Fatebinder [Player Name]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>10</ID>
      <DefaultText>Fatebinder Rhogalus,

You ask how an Archon died and I provide but one answer: by my hand.

My ushering [url=glossary:cairn]Cairn[/url] to the void stands as merely the most recent testament to my growing glory.

I am making a career of ending the unendable.

See you at court.

- Fatebinder [Player Name]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>11</ID>
      <DefaultText>Dear Fatebinder Rhogalus,

I took no satisfaction in ending [url=glossary:cairn]Cairn[/url] save that which one takes in fulfilling their obligations. The Archon of Stone's presence poisoned the [url=glossary:stone sea]Stone Sea[/url], his death throes hourly rocking the people of old Azure. Never have I seen so much suffering caused by the choices of a sole individual.

In executing the Archon of Stone, I both rid the [url=glossary:stone sea]Stone Sea[/url] of his protracted corrosion and released him from his agony. It had to be done, but there was no pleasure in it.

Until we meet again.

- Fatebinder [Player Name]</DefaultText>
