    <Entry>
      <ID>22</ID>
      <DefaultText>Fatebinder [Player Name],

Unless I am mistaken - and I am very rarely mistaken - I detect in your words remorse. Empathy, though an admirable trait, is wasted on the undeserving. One profits from fretting over the fates of the seditious no more than one profits from concern for the pain suffered by the murderer consigned to the headsman's axe. 

[url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url] has branded greater lands than Azure with the lingering effects of Edicts. We celebrate such destruction no more than we celebrate a verdict of guilt. They are no more and no less than the currency by which we purchase order and peace.

Thank you for your response and your continued service.

- Fatebinder Rhogalus</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>23</ID>
      <DefaultText>Fatebinder [Player Name],

Fascinating! One day we should stroll the remnant streets of the warehouse district and discuss the working of the Earthshakers in greater detail. 

Your desire for a "new order" elicits some concern. Do remember that whatever we craft here we erect to the glory of the Overlord.

- Fatebinder Rhogalus</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>24</ID>
      <DefaultText>Fatebinder [Player Name],

Fascinating! Such complex rites - requiring numerous trained magicians carefully shaping sigils with slight variations and specific foci - have historically presented difficulties when confronted by the unexpected. I am gladdened that you were able to interrupt the Earthshaker plot. Only [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url] knows what madness they had planned for that colossal stone corpse. 

Thank you for your response and your continued service.

- Fatebinder Rhogalus
</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>25</ID>
      <DefaultText>Fatebinder [Player Name],

I would caution you against hubris, but such warnings often go unheeded by those they would most benefit.

- Fatebinder Rhogalus</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>26</ID>
      <DefaultText>Dear Fatebinder [Player Name],

The Overlord's subjects watch the pronouncements of the Fatebinder and often see only pampered courtiers exalted by whim to parse the guilty from the guiltless. They rarely recognize the toll: the drudgery of study, the labor of training, the toil of investigating innocence and culpability.

Our efforts rarely earn praise. Nor should they. The death of an Archon deserves no more celebration than a verdict of guilt. They are no more and no less than the rings by which we purchase order and peace.

It heartens me that you discerned some moral remuneration in your duties. Remember, though, that our service to the Overlord demands uncompromising adherence to justice, not kindness or gallantry.

Thank you for your response and your continued service.

- Fatebinder Rhogalus</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
